From: Shelley Vohr <shelley.vohr@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 18:54:36 +0000
Subject: fix: bind new GlobalShortcuts portal commands when session is
 already up to date

When ListShortcuts reveals that every bound command is already registered
with the portal, OnListShortcuts returns without calling BindShortcuts and
bind_state_ stays kNotBound. A later OnCommandsChanged() with a live
session then matches neither the kBindCalled nor the kBound branch, so
newly added commands are silently never bound - registration appears to
succeed but the shortcuts never fire. Mark the session as bound in that
case so the next commands change re-creates the session and runs the bind
pass.

Upstreamable as a standalone fix; this affects any consumer registering a
command after startup when all previous commands were already approved.

diff --git a/ui/base/accelerators/global_accelerator_listener/global_accelerator_listener_linux.cc b/ui/base/accelerators/global_accelerator_listener/global_accelerator_listener_linux.cc
index 59150acea1fa6c9558c2f7e155a5bf9c9b195df2..dd53a82cd8d2e9a938373953eb6f0a9e43b59556 100644
--- a/ui/base/accelerators/global_accelerator_listener/global_accelerator_listener_linux.cc
+++ b/ui/base/accelerators/global_accelerator_listener/global_accelerator_listener_linux.cc
@@ -294,6 +294,12 @@ void GlobalAcceleratorListenerLinux::OnListShortcuts(
       return;
     }
   }
+
+  // All commands are already registered with the portal. Mark the session as
+  // bound so that a later OnCommandsChanged() with new commands re-creates
+  // the session and runs the bind pass; otherwise the state machine has no
+  // branch that would ever bind them.
+  bind_state_ = BindState::kBound;
 }
 
 void GlobalAcceleratorListenerLinux::BindShortcuts(DbusShortcuts old_shortcuts,
